svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 26, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104pqh1665703211678.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pqh1665703211678.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pqh1665703211678.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"pqh1665703211678\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">Integration Logicals\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface uses the following logicals to control how it connects with the JavaVirtual Machine, email servers, and the Sentinel Cloud Server.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pqh1665703211678__section_N1001A_N10017_N10001\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"pqh1665703211678__table_d16376e1_d16377e1_d16378e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Uniface Logicals</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"pqh1665703211678__table_d16376e1_d16377e1_d16378e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Logical</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"pqh1665703211678__table_d16376e1_d16377e1_d16378e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Description</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"pqh1665703211678__table_d16376e1_d16377e1_d16378e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">More Information</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqh1665703211678__table_d16376e1_d16377e1_d16378e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"iey1665703199519.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iey1665703199519.html\" title=\"Uniface logical for setting options for the Java Virtual Machine used in XSLT transformations.\">JVM_OPTIONS</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqh1665703211678__table_d16376e1_d16377e1_d16378e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Set the options for the Java Virtual Machine for XML transformations</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqh1665703211678__table_d16376e1_d16377e1_d16378e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ria1665702906209.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ria1665702906209.html\" title=\"Transform an XML stream using an XSLT style sheet.\">XMLTRANSFORM</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqh1665703211678__table_d16376e1_d16377e1_d16378e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jwm1665702907702.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jwm1665702907702.html\" title=\"Uniface logical that specifies how the initial message from the client is sent to an ESMTP server via the AUTH NTLM security driver.\">NTLM_INITIAL_RESPONSE</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqh1665703211678__table_d16376e1_d16377e1_d16378e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Specify how the initial message from the client is sent to an SMTP server via the AUTH NTLM security driver.</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqh1665703211678__table_d16376e1_d16377e1_d16378e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lqo1665702907563.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lqo1665702907563.html\" title=\"The Uniface AUTH NTLM security driver provides SMTP authentication using the Microsoft NT LAN Manager protocol.\">SMTP AUTH NTLM Security Driver</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xva1665702907828.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xva1665702907828.html\" title=\"The Uniface SSPI security driver is a Windows-specific driver that enables you to use the NTLM or Kerberos protocols for SMTP authentication. The driver uses the Windows Security Support Provider Interface (SSPI).\">SMTP SSPI Security Driver</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqh1665703211678__table_d16376e1_d16377e1_d16378e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jxw1665702547126.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jxw1665702547126.html\" title=\"Uniface logical that determines the default authentication schema to be used by the web server when processing UHTTP SEND requests.\">UHTTP_DEF_AUTH</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqh1665703211678__table_d16376e1_d16377e1_d16378e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Set the default authentication to be used by web server when processing UHTTP <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">SEND</span> operations</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqh1665703211678__table_d16376e1_d16377e1_d16378e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"luk1665703181080.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/luk1665703181080.html\" title=\"The UHTTP component is used to send requests to a web server, often via a proxy server. One or both servers may require user credentials to authenticate the request.\">Authentication with UHTTP</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"unt1665702546031.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/unt1665702546031.html\" title=\"Send an HTTP request.\">SEND</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqh1665703211678__table_d16376e1_d16377e1_d16378e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rxt1665702547215.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rxt1665702547215.html\" title=\"Uniface logical that, on Windows platforms only, determines whether a default Content-Type header is added to POST requests.\">UHTTP_WPOST_FORM</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqh1665703211678__table_d16376e1_d16377e1_d16378e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">On Windows platforms only, determines whether a default <code class=\"ph codeph\">Content-Type</code> header is added to <code class=\"ph codeph\">POST</code> requests.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">If set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">T</code>, a default <code class=\"ph codeph\">Content-Type</code> header is added.</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqh1665703211678__table_d16376e1_d16377e1_d16378e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"unt1665702546031.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/unt1665702546031.html\" title=\"Send an HTTP request.\">SEND</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqh1665703211678__table_d16376e1_d16377e1_d16378e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wpf1665702746449.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wpf1665702746449.html\" title=\"Uniface logical for setting the Uniface License Management utility (ULIC) to timeout if no response is received after a given period of time when connecting to the Sentinel Cloud Server.\">ULIC_TIMEOUT</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqh1665703211678__table_d16376e1_d16377e1_d16378e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Set a timeout on Uniface License Management utility (ULIC) when connecting to the Sentinel Cloud Server to activate or return a Sentinel cloud license.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">By default this is set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">2</code> minutes.</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"pqh1665703211678__table_d16376e1_d16377e1_d16378e1__entry__3\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qgt1690346679212.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qgt1690346679212.html\" title=\"The Uniface License Management utility (ulic) is responsible for activating and downloading required Sentinel licenses, for checking out licenses, and renewing the lease on licenses on a regular basis. The licenses themselves are maintained by the Sentinel Cloud Server.\">Uniface License Management Utility (ulic)</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531024\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531024\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Integration Logicals Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 26, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Integration Logicals Uniface uses the following logicals to control how it connects with the JavaVirtual Machine, email servers, and the Sentinel Cloud Server. Table 1. Uniface Logicals Logical Description More Information JVM_OPTIONS Set the options for the Java Virtual Machine for XML transformations XMLTRANSFORM NTLM_INITIAL_RESPONSE Specify how the initial message from the client is sent to an SMTP server via the AUTH NTLM security driver. SMTP AUTH NTLM Security Driver SMTP SSPI Security Driver UHTTP_DEF_AUTH Set the default authentication to be used by web server when processing UHTTP SEND operations Authentication with UHTTP SEND UHTTP_WPOST_FORM On Windows platforms only, determines whether a default Content-Type header is added to POST requests. If set to T , a default Content-Type header is added. SEND ULIC_TIMEOUT Set a timeout on Uniface License Management utility (ULIC) when connecting to the Sentinel Cloud Server to activate or return a Sentinel cloud license. By default this is set to 2 minutes. Uniface License Management Utility (ulic) Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}